The Kenya Film Classification Board is lobbying MPs to pass laws establishing a special police unit to curb child pornography and other social vices.The board also wants to have prosecutorial powers to arrest and prosecute those involved in child pornography.CEO Ezekiel Mutua on Tuesday said foreigners who engage in the vice should be deported.The board has engaged the IG and DPP&rsquo;s offices, who, according to sources, have responded positively.Two weeks ago, the board floated the idea to the National Assembly Committee on Labour and Social Welfare.They want the MPs to have legal provisions for the set-up of the special police unit and the prosecutorial powers before Parliament is dissolved.